TOTAL POPULATION - TOTAL POPULATION COMPRISES S'PORE RESIDENTS & NON-RESIDENTS.  RESIDENT POPULATION COMPRISES S'PORE CITIZENS & PERMANENT RESIDENTS.  DATA PRIOR TO 1990 ARE BASED ON DE FACTO CONCEPT (I.E. THE PERSON IS PRESENT IN THE COUNTRY AT THE REFERENCE PERIOD), WHILE DATA FROM 1990 ONWARDS ARE BASED ON DE JURE CONCEPT (I.E. THE PERSON'S PLACE OF USUAL RESIDENCE).  DATA FROM 2003 ONWARDS EXCLUDE RESIDENTS WHO ARE OVERSEAS FOR A CONTINUOUS PERIOD OF 12 MONTHS OR LONGER AS AT THE REFERENCE PERIOD.

RESIDENT POPULATION - DATA ARE AS AT END-JUNE.  DATA PRIOR TO 1990 ARE BASED ON DE FACTO CONCEPT (I.E. THE PERSON IS PRESENT IN THE COUNTRY AT THE REFERENCE PERIOD), WHILE DATA FROM 1990 ONWARDS ARE BASED ON DE JURE CONCEPT (I.E. THE PERSON'S PLACE OF USUAL RESIDENCE).  DATA FROM 2003 ONWARDS EXCLUDE RESIDENTS WHO ARE OVERSEAS FOR A CONTINUOUS PERIOD OF 12 MONTHS OR LONGER AS AT THE REFERENCE PERIOD.

SINGAPORE CITIZEN POPULATION - DATA ARE AS AT END-JUNE.  DATA PRIOR TO 1990 ARE BASED ON DE FACTO CONCEPT (I.E. THE PERSON IS PRESENT IN THE COUNTRY AT THE REFERENCE PERIOD), WHILE DATA FROM 1990 ONWARDS ARE BASED ON DE JURE CONCEPT (I.E. THE PERSON'S PLACE OF USUAL RESIDENCE).  DATA FROM 2003 ONWARDS EXCLUDE CITIZENS WHO ARE OVERSEAS FOR A CONTINUOUS PERIOD OF 12 MONTHS OR LONGER AS AT THE REFERENCE PERIOD.

PERMANENT RESIDENT POPULATION - DATA ARE AS AT END-JUNE.  DATA PRIOR TO 1990 ARE BASED ON DE FACTO CONCEPT (I.E. THE PERSON IS PRESENT IN THE COUNTRY AT THE REFERENCE PERIOD), WHILE DATA FROM 1990 ONWARDS ARE BASED ON DE JURE CONCEPT (I.E. THE PERSON'S PLACE OF USUAL RESIDENCE).  DATA FROM 2003 ONWARDS EXCLUDE PERMANENT RESIDENTS WHO ARE OVERSEAS FOR A CONTINUOUS PERIOD OF 12 MONTHS OR LONGER AS AT THE REFERENCE PERIOD.

NON-RESIDENT POPULATION - DATA ARE AS AT END-JUNE.  NON-RESIDENT POPULATION COMPRISES FOREIGNERS WHO WERE WORKING, STUDYING OR LIVING IN SINGAPORE BUT NOT GRANTED PERMANENT RESIDENCE, EXCLUDING TOURISTS AND SHORT-TERM VISITORS.

TOTAL POPULATION GROWTH - FOR CENSUS YEARS OF 1970, 1980 AND 1990, DATA REFER TO ANNUALISED GROWTH RATES OVER THE PREVIOUS CENSUS YEAR OF 1957, 1970 AND 1980 RESPECTIVELY.  DATA FOR 1990 AND EARLIER ARE COMPUTED USING POPULATION ESTIMATES BASED ON DE FACTO CONCEPT (I.E. THE PERSON IS PRESENT IN THE COUNTRY AT THE REFERENCE PERIOD), WHILE DATA FROM 1991 ONWARDS ARE BASED ON DE JURE CONCEPT (I.E. THE PERSON'S PLACE OF USUAL RESIDENCE).  FIGURE FOR 2003 IS COMPUTED BASED ON THE 2003 UNREVISED POPULATION WHICH INCLUDE RESIDENTS WHO ARE OVERSEAS FOR A CONTINUOUS PERIOD OF 12 MONTHS OR LONGER AS AT THE REFERENCE PERIOD.

RESIDENT POPULATION GROWTH - FOR CENSUS YEARS OF 1980 AND 1990, DATA REFER TO ANNUALISED GROWTH RATES OVER THE PREVIOUS CENSUS YEAR OF 1970 AND 1980 RESPECTIVELY.  DATA FOR 1990 AND EARLIER ARE COMPUTED USING POPULATION ESTIMATES BASED ON DE FACTO CONCEPT (I.E. THE PERSON IS PRESENT IN THE COUNTRY AT THE REFERENCE PERIOD), WHILE DATA FROM 1991 ONWARDS ARE BASED ON DE JURE CONCEPT (I.E. THE PERSON'S PLACE OF USUAL RESIDENCE).  FIGURE FOR 2003 IS COMPUTED BASED ON THE 2003 UNREVISED POPULATION WHICH INCLUDE RESIDENTS WHO ARE OVERSEAS FOR A CONTINUOUS PERIOD OF 12 MONTHS OR LONGER AS AT THE REFERENCE PERIOD.
POPULATION DENSITY - PRIOR TO 2003, DATA ARE BASED ON SINGAPORE'S LAND AREA AS AT END-DECEMBER.  FROM 2003 ONWARDS, DATA ARE BASED ON SINGAPORE?S LAND AREA AS AT END-JUNE.
SEX RATIO - DATA PRIOR TO 1980 (EXCEPT 1970) PERTAIN TO TOTAL POPULATION.  DATA FOR 1970 AND FROM 1980 ONWARDS PERTAIN TO SINGAPORE RESIDENTS (CITIZENS AND PERMANENT RESIDENTS).

MEDIAN AGE OF RESIDENT POPULATION - DATA PRIOR TO 1980 (EXCEPT 1970) PERTAIN TO TOTAL POPULATION.  DATA FOR 1970 AND FROM 1980 ONWARDS PERTAIN TO SINGAPORE RESIDENTS (CITIZENS AND PERMANENT RESIDENTS).
MEDIAN AGE OF CITIZEN POPULATION - DATA PERTAIN TO CITIZEN POPULATION.

OLD-AGE SUPPORT RATIO: RESIDENTS AGED 15-64 YEARS - DATA PRIOR TO 1980 (EXCEPT 1970) PERTAIN TO TOTAL POPULATION.  DATA FOR 1970 AND FROM 1980 ONWARDS PERTAIN TO SINGAPORE RESIDENTS (CITIZENS AND PERMANENT RESIDENTS).

AGE DEPENDENCY RATIO: RESIDENTS AGED UNDER 15 YEARS AND 65 YEARS - DATA PRIOR TO 1980 (EXCEPT 1970) PERTAIN TO TOTAL POPULATION.  DATA FOR 1970 AND FROM 1980 ONWARDS PERTAIN TO SINGAPORE RESIDENTS (CITIZENS AND PERMANENT RESIDENTS).

CHILD DEPENDENCY RATIO: RESIDENTS AGED UNDER 15 YEARS - DATA PRIOR TO 1980 (EXCEPT 1970) PERTAIN TO TOTAL POPULATION.  DATA FOR 1970 AND FROM 1980 ONWARDS PERTAIN TO SINGAPORE RESIDENTS (CITIZENS AND PERMANENT RESIDENTS).

OLD-AGE DEPENDENCY RATIO: RESIDENTS AGED 65 YEARS & OVER - DATA PRIOR TO 1980 (EXCEPT 1970) PERTAIN TO TOTAL POPULATION.  DATA FOR 1970 AND FROM 1980 ONWARDS PERTAIN TO SINGAPORE RESIDENTS (CITIZENS AND PERMANENT RESIDENTS).

OLD-AGE SUPPORT RATIO: RESIDENTS AGED 20-64 YEARS - DATA PRIOR TO 1980 (EXCEPT 1970) PERTAIN TO TOTAL POPULATION.  DATA FOR 1970 AND FROM 1980 ONWARDS PERTAIN TO SINGAPORE RESIDENTS (CITIZENS AND PERMANENT RESIDENTS).

AGE DEPENDENCY RATIO: RESIDENTS AGED UNDER 20 YEARS AND 65 YEARS & OVER - DATA PRIOR TO 1980 (EXCEPT 1970) PERTAIN TO TOTAL POPULATION.  DATA FOR 1970 AND FROM 1980 ONWARDS PERTAIN TO SINGAPORE RESIDENTS (CITIZENS AND PERMANENT RESIDENTS).

CHILD DEPENDENCY RATIO: RESIDENTS AGED UNDER 20 YEARS - DATA PRIOR TO 1980 (EXCEPT 1970) PERTAIN TO TOTAL POPULATION.  DATA FOR 1970 AND FROM 1980 ONWARDS PERTAIN TO SINGAPORE RESIDENTS (CITIZENS AND PERMANENT RESIDENTS).

OLD-AGE DEPENDENCY RATIO: RESIDENTS AGED 65 YEARS & OVER - DATA PRIOR TO 1980 (EXCEPT 1970) PERTAIN TO TOTAL POPULATION.  DATA FOR 1970 AND FROM 1980 ONWARDS PERTAIN TO SINGAPORE RESIDENTS (CITIZENS AND PERMANENT RESIDENTS).
OLD-AGE SUPPORT RATIO: CITIZENS AGED 15-64 YEARS - DATA PERTAIN TO CITIZEN POPULATION.
AGE DEPENDENCY RATIO: CITIZENS AGED UNDER 15 YEARS AND 65 YEARS & OVER - DATA PERTAIN TO CITIZEN POPULATION.
CHILD DEPENDENCY RATIO: CITIZENS AGED UNDER 15 YEARS - DATA PERTAIN TO CITIZEN POPULATION.
OLD-AGE DEPENDENCY RATIO: CITIZENS AGED 65 YEARS & OVER - DATA PERTAIN TO CITIZEN POPULATION.
OLD-AGE SUPPORT RATIO: CITIZENS AGED 20-64 YEARS - DATA PERTAIN TO CITIZEN POPULATION.
AGE DEPENDENCY RATIO: CITIZENS AGED UNDER 20 YEARS AND 65 YEARS & OVER - DATA PERTAIN TO CITIZEN POPULATION.
CHILD DEPENDENCY RATIO: CITIZENS AGED UNDER 20 YEARS - DATA PERTAIN TO CITIZEN POPULATION.
OLD-AGE DEPENDENCY RATIO: CITIZENS AGED 65 YEARS & OVER - DATA PERTAIN TO CITIZEN POPULATION.
NATURAL INCREASE - DATA PERTAIN TO TOTAL POPULATION.
RATE OF NATURAL INCREASE - DATA PRIOR TO 1980 PERTAIN TO TOTAL POPULATION.  DATA FROM 1980 ONWARDS PERTAIN TO RESIDENT POPULATION (I.E. SINGAPORE CITIZENS AND PERMANENT RESIDENTS).
